{"key":"processedPost-15481471","value":{"id":15481471,"first":15479254,"last":15484492,"when":1323303796,"utime":"12/08/11 02:23 AM","content":"The primary benefit of a sterilizer is it pulls a vacuum after cool-down, which prevents contaminants being drawn into the unit.&nbsp; If you're only using jars with filters, or spawn bags with tyvek wrist sleeves inserted as shown in Let's Grow Mushrooms, then a pressure cooker will work just as well and save money.<br />A secondary benefit of a sterilizer if you get one with self-contained heating element and thermostat is it will automatically maintain the desired pressure, and you don't need to mess with a stove control.<br />I use my AA75X sterilizers for grain spawn, and my AA921 pressure cooker for agar.&nbsp; You definitely don't want a sterilizer for agar or it will boil over and make a mess.<br />RR","title":"Re: All American PC or Sterilizer"}}